window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The full inside story of the technology paradigm shift transforming the food we eat and who is making it</b></p> <p>Ultraprocessed and secretly produced foods are roaring back into vogue, cheered by consumers and investors because they are plant-based and help address societal issues. And as our food system leaps ahead to a sterilized lab of the future, we think we know more about our food than we ever did, but because so much is happening so rapidly, we actually know less. In <i>Technically Food</i>, investigative reporter Larissa Zimberoﬀ pokes holes in the marketing mania behind today’s changing food landscape and clearly shows the trade-oﬀs of replacing real food with technology-driven approximations with news-breaking revelations.</p>"; 
